History & Authorship of microscotaspy:

The core functionalities of the microscotaspy package were originally
created at Boston University in 2017 in support of the Living
Computing Project.

The main authors of the microscotaspy package are:

  Timothy Jones.


Development of the microscotaspy was partially supported by NSF
Expeditions in Computing Award #1522074; all views and conclusions
embodied in this distribution are those of the authors and not NSF or
the U.S. Government.
